Left Join 

	A LEFT JOIN (or LEFT OUTER JOIN) in SQL is used to combine rows from two tables-
	Returns all rows from the left table, and Matching rows from the right table.
	If there is no match in the right table, it returns NULL for right table columns.
	Left table = the table written before LEFT JOIN.
	
	Employee - emp_id, emp_name, dept_id
	Department - dept_id, dept_name
	
	SELECT e.emp_id, e.emp_name, d.dept_name
	FROM employee e
	LEFT JOIN department d
	ON e.dept_id = d.dept_id;